  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Executive Engineer (Electrical Network Operations & Services)",
  "description": "<p><strong>What You'll Do:</strong></p><ol><li>Supervise a team of service technicians to attend to distribution network incident</li><li>Manage and facilitate with site officers to resolve network incident</li><li>Handle and resolve customer feedback and complaint.</li><li>Prepare incident reports to management and regulator on voltage dips / supply interruptions</li><li>Prepare monthly and weekly reports for submission to management</li><li>Carry out vehicle maintenance and servicing of company vehicles</li><li>Initiate purchase requestion for tools and other equipment</li><li>Assist Head of Section in maintenance of office facilities</li><li>Plan and arrange training for Electricity Service Centre (ESC) staff</li><li>Perform standby duty after office hours</li><li>Liaise with authorities and government agencies on network incident matters</li><li>Plan operation policy & strategies</li><li>Assist in budget preparation for the section</li><li>Perform any other duties related to the job scope</li></ol><p><strong>What You'll Need</strong></p><ol><li>Degree in Electrical Engineering or equivalent discipline from recognised university by PEB, Singapore.</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office Word, Excel and PowerPoint applications.</li><li>Able to handle customers’ request</li><li>Good oral and written communication skills.</li><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, resourceful and meticulous</li><li>Highly motivated and pro-active with the ability to work both independently as well as in a team</li></ol>",
